---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 14
  Paragraph: 38
Title: The Turning Of Heaven
---
Tzu-kung said, "Then is it true that the Perfect Man can command
corpse-like stillness and dragon vision, the voice of thunder and the
silence of deep pools; that he breaks forth into movement like Heaven
and earth? If only I too could get to see him!"
